The slate-colored antbird (Myrmelastes schistaceus) is a species of bird in the family Thamnophilidae.
It is found in Brazil, Colombia, Ecuador, and Peru.
Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest.
The slate-colored antbird was described by the English zoologist Philip Sclater in 1858 and given the binomial name Hypnocmenis schistacea.